SIMPLE: incorporate
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporate
<hw>In*cor"po*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incorporatus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Corporate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not consisting of matter; not having a material
body; incorporeal; spiritual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Moses forbore to speak of angles, and things invisible, and
<qex>incorporate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not incorporated; not existing as a corporation;
<as>as, an <ex>incorporate</ex> banking association</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporate
<hw>In*cor"po*rate</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>incorporatus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>incorporare</ets> to incorporate; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in
+ <ets>corporare</ets> to make into a body. See
<er>Corporate</er>.]</ety> <def>Corporate; incorporated; made one body,
or united in one body; associated; mixed together; combined;
embodied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if our hands, our sides, voices, and minds⟦br⟧
Had been <qex>incorporate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fifteenth part of silver <qex>incorporate</qex> with gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporate
<hw>In*cor"po*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Incorporated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Incorporating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To form into a body; to combine, as different
ingredients, into one consistent mass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By your leaves, you shall not stay alone,⟦br⟧
Till holy church <qex>incorporate</qex> two in one.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To unite with a material body; to give a material
form to; to embody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The idolaters, who worshiped their images as gods, supposed some
spirit to be <qex>incorporated</qex> therein.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To unite with, or introduce into, a mass already
formed; <as>as, to <ex>incorporate</ex> copper with silver</as>; -- used
with <ptcl>with</ptcl> and <ptcl>into</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To unite intimately; to blend; to assimilate; to
combine into a structure or organization, whether material or mental;
<as>as, to <ex>incorporate</ex> provinces into the realm; to
<ex>incorporate</ex> another's ideas into one's work.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Romans did not subdue a country to put the inhabitants to fire
and sword, but to <qex>incorporate</qex> them into their own
community.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To form into a legal body, or body politic; to
constitute into a corporation recognized by law, with special functions,
rights, duties and liabilities; <as>as, to <ex>incorporate</ex> a bank,
a railroad company, a city or town, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporate
<hw>In*cor"po*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To unite in
one body so as to make a part of it; to be mixed or blended; -- usually
followed by <xex>with</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Painters' colors and ashes do better <qex>incorporate</qex> will
oil.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He never suffers wrong so long to grow,⟦br⟧
And to <qex>incorporate</qex> with right so far⟦br⟧
As it might come to seem the same in show.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporated</ent>⟦br⟧
